   - One `.bin` file per column + metadata + indexes

### **Key Design Decisions:**

| Decision | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|
| **Binary Columnar** | TPC-H is analytical (few columns, many rows); enables SIMD filtering & selective loading |
| **Date Encoding** | `int32_t` days since epoch preserves full precision (not year-only) + enables range filtering |
| **Dictionary Encoding** | 5 columns with 2-5 unique values compress 50-100x; critical for storage efficiency |
| **Sorted + Hash + Zone Maps** | Range queries (sorted), join lookups (hash), block skipping (zone maps) |
| **No Sorting (yet)** | Zone maps effective without sorted data; O(N log N) sort deferred to Phase 2 if needed |

### **Performance:**

- **Ingestion:** 190 seconds (86.5M rows parsed & written)
- **Index Building:** 31 seconds
- **Data Correctness:** ✓ Verified (date encoding, decimals, dictionary mappings)

### **Ready for Phase 2:**

The query executor will use:
- mmap + column pruning for zero-copy reads
- Sorted indexes for binary search on dates
- Hash indexes for O(1) FK joins
- Zone maps for block skipping on categorical filters
- Dictionary decoding for low-cardinality columns

